<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pantani Wins 13th Stage at Tour de France </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Italian Marco Pantani won the 13th
stage of the Tour de France when the race reached at Alpe d'Huez,
France, on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Pantani, who won a stage at the same Alpine finish in 1995,
beat yellow jersey holder Jan Ullrich of Germany to second place
at 46 seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Ullrich increased his overall lead ahead of Frenchman Richard
Virenque, who was third in the stage with one minute 27 seconds
behind Pantani, to six minutes 22 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Defending champion Bjarne Riis of Denmark and Spainiard Abraham
Olano were third place overall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
