<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Regional Transport Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Zimbabwe will next week host a
conference on regional harmonization of transport and
communication systems in the southern African region.
</P>
<P>
The conference to be hosted by the Zimbabwe National Chamber
of Commerce (ZNCC) runs from July 22 to 24 in the northern resort
town of Victoria Falls.
</P>
<P>
ZNCC President Danny Meyer today said about 140 participants
from ministries of transport, posts and telecommunications,
transport operators, chambers of commerce, trade associations,
freight forwarders and importers and exporters are expected to
attend the three-day conference.
</P>
<P>
Meyer said the meeting will discuss harmonization of freight
market access policies, transport communication systems, rail
transport charges, Beira seaport facilities, improving the
marketability of rail transport in the sub-region, and role of
the private sector in transport and communication systems as an
engine for growth. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
