<HEADLINE> Three People Killed in Summer Storms in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed, trees
uprooted and power lines knocked down in a Summer storm that
flashed across New York Metropolitan region Friday, according to a
report of the New York Times Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The storms, some with near hurricane-force wind, battered the
region from central New Jersey to eastern long Island in two
rounds-- the first in the afternoon, the second in the evening.
</P>
<P>
The area's three major airports reported delays of up to an
hour or more.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few days, New Yorkers had been plaqued by heat
waves that pushed the temperatures as high as more than 90 degree
Fahrenheit. 41 people had been taken to hospitals for heat-related
problems. Some areas reported shortages of electricity and water
supplies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
