<HEADLINE> Syrian President Meets Belarussian FM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Syrian President Hafez Assad
held a meeting here this afternoon with visiting Belarussian
Foreign Minister Ivan Antonovich.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Antonovich emphasized that Israel should
withdraw from the entire Syrian Golan Heights and the rest of
occupied Arab territories, in implementation of the relevant
U.N. resolutions, a spokesman for the Syrian presidency said.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Foreign Minister Farouq al Shara had earlier had
official talks with Antonovich, who arrived here Friday on an
official visit, on the situation in the Middle East and Europe.
</P>
<P>
Upon his arrival here, Antonovich told reporters that his
current visit to Syria was intended to boost bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
"We view with great respect Syria's struggle for sovereignty
and for the establishment of a fair peace in the region," the
Belarussian foreign minister said. 
</P>
