<HEADLINE> Chiluba Urges Rwandans to Forget Past </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba today urged Rwandans to forget their past sufferings and
forge ahead to ensure the development of their country.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba made the appeal when he received credentials from new
Rwandan Ambassador Joy Mukanyange, radio Zambia reported.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba called for further stepped up relations between the
two countries for the benefit of the two peoples.
</P>
<P>
He said Zambia appreciated the efforts by the Rwandan
government to revive the country's economic development lost in
the past days.
</P>
<P>
In turn, Mukanyange said Rwanda greatly appreciated Zambia's
efforts to help bring peace to his country.
</P>
<P>
The ambassador also called for strengthening bilateral ties.
</P>
<P>
Half a million Rwandan people were killed in 1994 when an
ethnic war broke out in the central African country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
