<HEADLINE> Zambian Students Need Improvement of Quality: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- A top geologist of the Zambia
Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM) has called for closer link
between the university students and industrial experts of the
country to improve the quality of graduates.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail paper today quoted Sixtiesd Mulenga as
saying in northern Zambia on Friday that it is saddening to note
that the graduates' performance in the field is unsatisfactory
due to lack of adequate exposure.
</P>
<P>
He said Zambia is currently moving toward a boom phase in
mineral exploration but there have been problems in finding
geologists to work with because of the lack of qualified staff.
</P>
<P>
He said that highly qualified lecturers should be appointed to
senior management levels.
</P>
<P>
He suggested that technical schools like the School of Mines
at the University of Zambia be re-located to the Copperbelt from
Lusaka to enable students to have access to the field, work in
the mines and meet experts who could lecture them. 
</P>
</TEXT>
