<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Italy to Promote Economic Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Italy will further
enhance bilateral trade and economic cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The message came from a meeting held here today by Pakistani
Finance Minister Sartaj Aziz with visiting Italian Deputy Foreign
Minister Patrizia Toia.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting the two sides discussed ways and means to
promote bilateral trade and economic cooperation in different
fields.
</P>
<P>
They also discussed the utilization of 19 million U.S dollars
of Italian assistance for which sectoral priorities would be
jointly determined.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they deliberated on the possibility of establishing
institutes for leather technology and textile designing in
Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Aziz briefed Toia on the economic policies pursued by the
Pakistani government for the revival of economy.
</P>
<P>
Toia appreciated the reforms process initiated by the Pakistani
government, particularly the economic packages recently announced
for economic revival.
</P>
<P>
She said that a special post is going to be created in the
Italian embassy in Pakistan to co-ordinate with Italian
entrepreneurs for investment in Pakistan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
