<P>
The two leaders signed a reconciliation agreement in Cairo on
May 29 on holding peaceful talks to end the civil war that has
ravaged the country since 1991. Egypt has been involved in
mediating an end to the crisis in the past few months.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League will pursue efforts that aim at making
mediation between various Somali factions a success, he was quoted
by the Egyptian MENA news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Members of the Somali National Salvation Council will shortly
make a tour of a number of Arab countries and states concerned
with the Somali crisis to gain support for their plan that aims at
achieving Somali reconciliation, the official said.
</P>
<P>
The Arab League is currently coordinating efforts with the UN
and the Organization of African Unity as well as major countries
in the area such as Egypt and Ethiopia to activate the Somali
reconciliation process.
</P>
<P>
Since the 1991 ouster of the late president Mohamed Siad Barre,
Somalia has been fragmented into fiefdoms protected by faction
leaders, who continued to fight to expand their turfs despite
several unsuccessful peace conferences.
</P>
<P>
The factional fighting, combined with a 1992 famine, has
claimed about 350,000 lives. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
