<HEADLINE> Italian President Visits Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Italian President Oscar Luigi
Scalfaro arrived in Saudi Arabia today on a two-day state visit,
the first by an Italian president in 23 years.
</P>
<P>
The Italian president who is accompanied by a senior
delegation including the Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini will hold
political as well as economic talks with Saudi King Fahd Ibn
Abdul-Aziz and other leaders, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait News Agency quoted Italian embassy sources in Saudi
Arbia as saying that Scalfaro's talks with Saudi leaders would
focus on regional and international developments, foremost the
stalemate in the peace process in the Middle East as well as the
bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
The talks would also deal with the situation in the Gulf and
its impact on stability and security in the region.
</P>
<P>
The sources added that Scalfaro's visit aims at promoting
cooperation between Italy and Saudi Arabia in various fields,
particularly in the economic, trade and investment domains.
</P>
<P>
The two countries signed a cooperation and investment
protection agreement during a visit to Saudi Arabia by Dini last
September. The agreement also banned dual taxation.
</P>
<P>
Trade exchanges between Saudi Arabia and Italy in 1995
amounted to 3.2 billion U.S. dollars with 747 million U.S. dollars
in Saudi favor, according to official figures.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have been also linked by a security pact
since December 1995 which stipulates joint cooperation in
combating organized crimes, drugs and terrorism. 
</P>
