<DOCNO> XIE19970720.0033 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Significant Sea Transportation Solution Between HK, Taiwan (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A signed article titled, "The
Significance and Enlightenment of the Solution to the Issue on Sea
Transportation between Hong Kong and Taiwan after 1997", carried
by the latest issue of the journal "Relations across the Straits",
says that the pragmatic settlement to the problem conforms both to
the one-China principle and the interests of compatriots in Hong
Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The smooth settlement of the issue of sea transportation is
beneficial to economic development and exchanges between Hong Kong
and Taiwan, the article says, and will play a role in showing the
way to developing direct shipping services across the Taiwan
Straits.
</P>
<P>
The article notes that on May 2 and 24, 1997 the Federation of
Hong Kong Shipowners and the Taiwan-based Straits Exchanges
Foundation exchanged views in Hong Kong and Taibei and reached an
understanding over the issue concerning flying of flags when ships
from both sides navigate between or enter each other's ports, and
the Summary Of Negotiations On Sea Transportation Between Hong
Kong and Taiwan was inked as a result.
</P>
<P>
The summary rules that after July 1, 1997 "Hong Kong-registered
commercial ships will fly only the regional flag of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) on the stern flagpole during
the period when they enter and exit Taiwan ports, and the flying
of flags from the main mast will be suspended pending further
consultation". Also, "Taiwan-registered commercial ships will fly
no flags temporarily on either the stern flagpole or the main mast
during the period when they enter or exit the port of Hong
Kong. The flying of flags will be decided upon through further
consultation."
</P>
<P>
The Summary of Negotiations has been examined and affirmed by
the mainland's Association for Relations across the Taiwan Straits
and the Straits Exchanges Foundation, and officially went into
effect on July 1.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
