<DOCNO> XIE19970720.0034 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Significant Solution to Sea Transportation Between HK, Taiwan (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The settlement of the sea transportation issue between Hong
Kong and Taiwan after 1997 has drawn strong repercussions in the
two places, the article says. The majority opinion of shipping
circles in the two places holds that the sea transportation
between Hong Kong and Taiwan remains unblocked after 1997 and this
is of great significance for the economic development of both Hong
Kong and Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The consultation on technical problems and the signing of the
summary reflected the principle of pragmatic practice and mutual
benefit, which complies with the interests of all parties
concerned. The Taiwan-based newspapers have spoken highly of the
negotiations, considering them successful and noting that smooth
navigation between Hong Kong and Taiwan ensures some 30 billion US
dollars-worth of annual trade between them.
</P>
<P>
The smooth solution to the sea transportation issue between
Hong Kong and Taiwan will play an exemplary and demonstrative role
in promoting direct shipping services between the motherland and
Taiwan in the following aspects:
</P>
<P>
First, the continuation of direct shipping between Hong Kong
and Taiwan has paved the way for realization of direct shipping
services across the Taiwan Straits. Since the return of Hong Kong
to the motherland this year, relations between Hong Kong and
Taiwan have become a special part of the relations between the two
sides of the Taiwan Straits. The people-to-people exchanges
between Hong Kong and Taiwan will be maintained and developed on
the basis of observing the Basic Law and the principle of One
China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
