<HEADLINE> Significant Solution to Sea Transportation Issue Between HK, Taiwan (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Direct shipping between Hong Kong and Taiwan will become a
component part of direct shipping between the motherland and
Taiwan. With further growth of economic, trade and cultural
exchanges between the motherland, Taiwan and Hong Kong, the
partial direct shipping will be extended from Hong Kong to other
parts of Taiwan and the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Secondly, the consultation over the technical issues of sea
transportation between Hong Kong and Taiwan after 1997 has
provided a model for the settlement of the relevant problems
existing in the upcoming direct shipping services between the two
sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
The article stressed that the One China principle is the basis
for maintaining and developing relations between Hong Kong and
Taiwan after 1997. As far as sea transportation is concerned, that
between the Hong Kong and Taiwan will remain unblocked providing
that the problem of Two Chinas or One China, One Taiwan does not
complicate the flag issue.
</P>
<P>
The article noted that the signing of the Summary of
Negotiations On Sea Transportation Between Hong Kong And Taiwan
fully reflected the sincerity, mutual respect, consultation on an
equal footing and pragmatism of the two sides. It has provided a
good example for resolving the issue of flags for direct shipping
across the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it will provide reference for the settlement of
the relevant technical problems in comprehensive direct shipping
services between the mainland and Taiwan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
