<HEADLINE> Corretja Wins Mercedes Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Spaniard Alex Corretja beat Slovakian
Karol Kucera 6-2, 7-5 to capture the title of the 1.04 million
U.S. dollars Mercedes Cup Sunday at Stuttgart, Germany.
</P>
<P>
Corretja took a 5-1 lead in the second set. But Kucera broke
Corretja's serve and won his three to shorten the gap to 5-6. But
Corretja finally prevented Kucera's coming-back to seal the match.
</P>
<P>
This is Corretja's fourth title in this season after he won at
Estoril, Portugal and Rome in April and May.
</P>
<P>
In addition to a cheque for 157,000 U.S. dollars, the third
seed also won a Mercedes SLK sportscar. Kucera collected 82,000
U.S. dollars in runner-up money.
</P>
<P>
Corretja, now ranked a career-high sixth on the ATP Tour, also
keeps the year's best win-loss record on clay of 37-12. 
</P>
</TEXT>
