<HEADLINE> S. Leone Junta and ECOWAS Reached Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FREETOWN, July 20 (Xinhua)- Sierra Leone junta delegation
attending mediation talks with four foreign ministers of the
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) returned here
Saturday with agreement to solve the country's political impasse
peacefully.
</P>
<P>
The 13 member delegation led by the junta's Foreign Secretary
Paolo Bangura had a two-day initial talks in Abidjan in which a
four-point agreement was reached, diplomatic sources said.
</P>
<P>
The meeting resolved that "all crises should be solved
peacefully, all hostilities cease with immediate effect that all
sides should work for an early restoration of constitutional
order and to give time to the junta delegation to report back to
military leader, Major Johnny Paul Koroma and reconvene the talks
in Abidjan on July 25."
</P>
<P>
In the Sierra Leone capital Saturday, hundred of people
welcome the decisions reached so far at the talks, assessing it
as a high degree looming on the horizon."
</P>
<P>
Military officers called the accord "a good beginning for
peace between Sierra Leone soldiers and a contingent of Nigerian
troops which have repeatedly clashed over the past two weeks at
the international airport and a major highway east of the
capital.
</P>
<P>
"We can not look forward to the Nigerians lifting their
blockade of the main highway, 20 miles from the capital which
leads to the interior", one soldier said.
</P>
<P>
The Nigerians blocked the highway after a conflict last
weekend which left some 60 people, mainly civilians dead.
</P>
<P>
The news of the talks, which is the first with any foreign
group since the junta came into power seven weeks ago, was
welcomed with relief in Bo in the south where an independent FM
station interrupted its regular programs to play victory songs.
</P>
<P>
In both Kenema and Kono in the east, marchers snake-danced at
the court halls in celebrations. The State radio also welcomed
the decisions as "a positive development". 
</P>
</TEXT>
