<HEADLINE> Rios Sets Highest Transfer-Record in Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Roberto Rios of Real Betis set the
highest transfer-record of two billion pesetas (13.5 million
U.S. dollars) in Spain to Athletic Bilbao, Spanish newspapers
reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Rios, 26, had played for Real Betis since 1992, capturing seven
caps to his name.
</P>
<P>
Manchester United earlier in the year offered a bid of 10.5
million U.S. dollars for the Spanish international defender, but
this offer was turned down.
</P>
<P>
Rios, however, was not the most expensive player signings made
by Spainsh clubs. Juninho tops the list as he moved from
Middlesbrough to Atletico Madrid with a record of 19.5 million
U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Christian Vieri was the second most expensive player after his
transfering from Juventus to Atletico Madrid with 17.5 million
U.S. dollars. Rios is the third.
</P>
<P>
Real Madrid's two Spanish international goalkeepers Francisco
Buyo and Jose Canizares are also transfer listed. Buyo is the
target of Rayo Vallecano and Mexican club Atletico Celya. He has
won seven Spanish caps during the 11 seasons in Real Madrid and 6
seasons with Sevilla.
</P>
<P>
Canizares leaves the Real for the coming of Pedro Contreras
from Rayo Vallecano. He manages to acquire nine caps. 
</P>
