<DOCNO> XIE19970720.0049 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chernobyl Project Tenders to Be Announced Soon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A group overseeing a renovation
project at the Chernobyl nuclear power plant is to announce
several tenders soon, First Deputy Energy Minister Mykola Friedman
said.
</P>
<P>
The group, which consists of U.S. consultants Westinghouse and
representatives of the Chernobyl station's management, is seeking
bids to supply equipment for reactor operation control,
radioactivity monitoring and power unit control, Friedman said.
</P>
<P>
Westinghouse won a tender on April 4 to supervise the work,
which is geared towards raising the plant's safety standards.
</P>
<P>
The project is being funded by an ECU 118 million grant from
the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development, and
Westinghouse is to be paid ECU 8.7 million for managing the
project.
</P>
<P>
As part of the project, ECU 13.5 million will be spent to
upgrade safety equipment of the plant's third reactor. A further
ECU 80 million will be used to construct a waste storage facility
and a reprocessing plant for liquid radioactive waste materials.
</P>
</TEXT>
