<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Accord Transit Facilities to Nepal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh's second largest port
Mongla is expected to become a regional port with Nepal having
transit facilities for shipment of its export and import cargoes
through Bangladesh in the near future, sources said today.
</P>
<P>
According to the sources, the Bangladeshi government has agreed
in principle to accord transit facilities to Nepal, upholding the
spirit of regional cooperation in expanding trade and improving
the livelihood of the people in the region.
</P>
<P>
An agreement allowing transit facilities to Nepal could be
finalized in the next few months, presumably before the year was
out, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
Nepal, an inland mountain country, has been showing interest in
obtaining the right for shipment of cargoes to pass through
Bangladesh. The main hurdle was the absence of any agreement for
passing through Indian territory between Bangladesh and Nepal.
</P>
<P>
The hurdle, however, was cleared recently with India agreeing
to allow the movement of Nepal's traffic through its territory to
and from Bangladesh.  
</P>
</TEXT>
