<HEADLINE> Central Authorities Hail Inner Mongolia on Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUHHOT, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The Central Committee of the
Communist Party of China (CPC), the Standing Committee of the
National People's Congress, the State Council, the National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference, and the Central Military Commission today sent a joint
message of congratulations to the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region
on the occasion of the 50th anniversary of its founding.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia, the first autonomous ethnic-minority region in
China, was a creation of the CPC, combining the fundamental tenets
of Marxism with China's multi-ethnic situation, and provided a
model for the implementation of autonomy in other areas of the
country, the message noted.
</P>
<P>
Great achievements have been made in socialist revolution and
construction over the past half a century in the region. Today's
Inner Mongolia enjoys political stability, economic expansion,
ethnic unity and social progress, it said.
</P>
<P>
The glorious experience of the autonomous region has shown that
in order to maintain the stability and development of the region,
efforts must be made to uphold Marxism and Leninism, Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping's Theory of Building Socialism with
Chinese Characteristics, and to unswervingly march along the road
socialism under the leadership of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
Also, the message stressed the need to focus on economic
construction along with efforts to deepen reforms, open wider to
the outside world, promote overall social progress, and to improve
people's material and cultural living standards.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the message said the Party's policies on ethnic
and religious affairs must be fully implemented, along with
efforts to safeguard ethnic and national unity, and social
stability.
</P>
<P>
The message called on regional efforts to come up with creative
work in combining the policy of the central government with the
realities of the region.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee and the State Council will continue
to give full support to the development of Inner Mongolia in the
future, the message asserted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
