<HEADLINE> Hainan Seeks Investment for Batch of Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 20 (Xinhua) -- South China's island province of
Hainan will attract investment for 100 projects, 23 of which have
been announced to the public.
</P>
<P>
The first batch of announced projects include five
infrastructure projects, ten industrial projects, six agricultural
projects and two tourism projects.
</P>
<P>
The infrastructure projects include the upgrading of the
urban electricity network, involving a total investment of 450
million yuan, and the handling of garbage in Sanya, involving
10.45 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Among the industrial projects are a 320-million-yuan polyester
fiber factory and a 664-million-yuan flour mill.
</P>
<P>
Major agricultural projects include a 500-million-yuan tropical
botanical garden and a tropical agriculture base, which will be
built at a cost of 96.3 million yuan.
</P>
<P>
In addition, an international holiday zone will be built at
Wuzhi Mountain, involving an investment of 150 million yuan, and
Yalong Bay in Sanya will set up a state-level tourism area with an
investment of 15 million yuan.  
</P>
