<HEADLINE> Haikou Improves Housing Conditions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that local
residents in this capital of China's southernmost Hainan Province
have made great progress in improving their housing conditions.
</P>
<P>
The per capita housing area of local residents has reached 13
sq m, up 85.7 percent from 1987, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
However, there are still seven percent of local families living
in overcrowded conditions, with each member having less than four
sq m of housing area, they said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, more than half of local families have telephones
today, and about 37 percent of them have the property rights to
their houses. 
</P>
