<HEADLINE> Jiangsu's Exports on Rise in First Half of 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics show that
the total export value of east China's Jiangsu Province reached
6.78 billion US dollars in the first half of this year.
</P>
<P>
The figure is up 26.2 percent from the same period of last
year, according to official sources.
</P>
<P>
This shows that the province has made a success of revamping
the mix of its export products, and most local export-oriented
enterprises have started making profits, they said.
</P>
<P>
The Jiangsu provincial government has taken measures to support
the development of the machine-building, electronics, chemical and
automobile industries since early this year to improve the
economic performance of local foreign trade enterprises.
</P>
<P>
As a result, the province's exports of finished industrial
products rose 0.3 percent in the first half of this year, and the
export value of these products accounted for 91.9 percent of the
province's total in the first six months.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Jiangsu saw a marginal growth in exports of
machinery and electronic products in the first half, accounting
for one third of the total export of finished industrial products.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
