<HEADLINE> Doohan Takes Sixth Consecutive Victory </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Australian Michael Doohan recorded
his sixth consecutive victory Sunday when he took the German 500cc
motorcycling grand prix in Nurburgring.
</P>
<P>
World champion Doohan on his Honda recovered from a poor start
and pulled clear of team mate Tadayuki Okada on the 12th lap to
take his eighth win of the season, out of nine races, reports
reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Okada was second place while fellow Japanese Takuma Aoki, also
on a Honda, came a distant third.
</P>
<P>
The victory allowed Doohan to extend his already almost
invincible lead at the top of the world championship standings.
</P>
<P>
The 32-year-old now has 220 points, 107 more than second-placed
Nobuatsu Aoki, who came fourth on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
With six races remaining before the end of the season, the
Australian, who has won the last three world championship crowns,
looks set to become the third man to win four 500c titles in
succession, after Mike Hailwood and Giacomo Agostini. 
</P>
