<HEADLINE> IACVB Conference a Vote of Confidence in Hong Kong, Says FS </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The choosing of Hong Kong by the
International Association of Convention and Visitor Bureaus
(IACVB) as the venue for its Annual Convention "is a vote of
confidence in Hong Kong as an international tourism, convention
and exhibition destination," Financial Secretary Donald Tsang of
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) said here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Officiating at the opening ceremony of the IACVB's 38th Annual
Convention and Asia-Pacific Sales Mission here today, Tsang said
that much of what Chinese President Jiang Zemin said of the "one
country, two systems" concept during ceremonies for Hong Kong's
return to China three weeks ago is already a reality.
</P>
<P>
"There may still be prophets of doom and gloom who predict Hong
Kong's star will fade. But I earnestly believe such predictions
are ill-founded, over simplistic and fail to give due
consideration of the determination of the Hong Kong people to
succeed and to seize the opportunities thrown up by new challenges
and circumstances, to the determination of China to make the Hong
Kong enterprise work," he said.
</P>
<P>
Tsang said that the elements of Hong Kong's success would not
change. "Come back next year, in five years or 10 years. You will
find Hong Kong's star shining even bigger, brighter and better
than before," he said.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the opening ceremony, Hong Kong Tourist Association
(HKTA)'s Executive Director Amy Chan said the IACVB's confidence
in Hong Kong set a good example for many international
organizations to follow. And now Hong Kong has many events
confirmed all the way to the year 2006.
</P>
<P>
She encouraged more interaction among HKTA's friends and
counterparts around the world because this would benefit everyone
involved in the tourist industry.
</P>
<P>
The three-day conference has a program including presentation
and keynote address, education sessions, and a business trip to
Macao.
</P>
<P>
The IACVB was founded in 1914 to promote professionalism in the
areas of destination marketing for both conventions and tourism.
Based in Washington DC, the organization, which now has 420 member
bureaus, brings together Convention and Visitor Bureau leaders
from 30 countries and regions for the Hong Kong conference. 
</P>
</TEXT>
