<HEADLINE> Inflation in India Down to 4.7 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 20 (Xinhua)-- India's annual inflation rate
plunged to a 52-week low of 4.70 percent for the week that ended
July 5 from 5.9 percent in the previous week, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The sharp decline was attributed to the "wearing off" of the
direct effect of last July's petroleum price hike on inflation.
During the corresponding week last year, the inflation rate had
jumped 1.6 percentage points to 5.8 percent on account of the
petro-product price hike.
</P>
<P>
Compared to the 4.70 percent inflation in all commodities, the
rate of increase in prices of "primary articles" was 4.03 percent,
while in "manufactured products" and fuel, power, light and
lubricants it was 4.35 percent and 8.45 percent respectively.
</P>
</TEXT>
