<HEADLINE> Central Government Pledges Support for Inner Mongolia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese leader said here
today that the Central government will increase its aid to the
Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region with increased revenues and
national strength.
</P>
<P>
"The central government's policy of helping the region speed up
development will remain unchanged," Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua told a
rally attended by more than 50,000 people to mark the 50th
anniversary of the founding of this autonomous region.
</P>
<P>
Zou, also a member of the Political Bureau of the Chinese
Communist Party Central Committee, is the head of the central
government delegation to Inner Mongolia.
</P>
<P>
Inner Mongolia, based on fifty years of development, with
abundant natural resources and with support of the central
government, is now facing a rare development opportunity and
enjoys bright prospects.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the primary task for the region is to focus on
economic development and to do its utmost to improve the living
standards of people of various ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
He asked the Party and government organizations in the region
to continue to strengthen the status of agriculture and animal
husbandry as the foundation of the region's economy, improve
production conditions, promote industrialized and intensive
production in rural and livestock-breeding areas by relying on
scientific and technological progress, so as to effectively
increase supplies of farm products and animal by-products, as well
as the incomes of local residents.
</P>
<P>
The agricultural and animal product processing industry, the
energy industry and the metallurgical industry must be given
priority in order to spur the overall economic growth of Inner
Mongolia, Zou said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that Inner Mongolia must stick to and improve the
system of regional autonomy. Its socialist legal system with the
characteristics of regional autonomy should be improved, so as to
be adapted to the market economic structure.
</P>
<P>
He said that the achievements made by Inner Mongolia in the
past 50 years are unprecedented in history.
</P>
<P>
"Strengthening unity among people of various ethnic groups,
maintaining social stability and safeguarding the unification of
the motherland are preconditions for invigorating Inner Mongolia,"
Zou said.
</P>
<P>
He asked officials and people of various ethnic groups in Inner
Mongolia to bear the general situation in mind, correctly handle
new circumstances and problems cropping up in the process of
development, properly deal with social contradictions detrimental
to unity and stability, in order to create a stable social
environment for the reform, opening up and economic construction,
and to safeguard the unification of the motherland and China's
long-term stability and prosperity.  
</P>
</TEXT>
