aiming at salvaging the peace process, which came to a halt as
Israel began building thousands of homes for Jews in East
Jerusalem in March.
</P>
<P>
Majali will convey a message from Jordan's King Hussein to
Palestinian National Authority President Yasser Arafat in a
meeting in the West Bank city of Ramallah today.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian premier told the Arabic-language radio that the
meeting with Arafat will cover their bilateral relations and the
latest developments of the peace drive.
</P>
<P>
The Jordanian monarch is expected in Cairo soon for talks with
President Hosni Mubarak on the current efforts to push ahead the
stalled peace march.
</P>
<P>
Egypt stepped in as a major mediator between the Palestinians
and Israelis as the U.S. efforts have visibly slacked off, failing
to bear pressure on Israel to halt its settlement activities.
</P>
<P>
Cairo has brokered a Palestinian-Israeli ministerial meeting in
Tel Aviv recently to discuss implementation of the agreement on
operating Gaza airport. An enlarged Egyptian-Palestinian meeting
will be held here on Sunday to evaluate the present situation.
