<HEADLINE> ASEAN Secretary General on ASEAN Financial Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 20 (Xinhua) -- ASEAN Secretary General Ajit
Singh said today that the seven ASEAN member states have to
contribute equally to its secretariat's annual budget of 6 million
U.S. dollars to keep it running.
</P>
<P>
Besides contributing about three quarters of one million U.S.
dollars, each member has other financial obligations like the
ASEAN Funds of one million U.S. dollars, and also the Science
Funds of about 500,000 U.S. dollars," he told the Malaysian
national news agency Bernama ahead of a two-day ASEAN senior
officials meeting here beginning tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
"There is no such thing as paying for membership. This is not a
club. This is an association and there is a budget for it and they
all have to share the budget equally," Ajit Singh was quoted as
saying.
</P>
<P>
He also said that in addition, ASEAN members have to make other
kinds of commitment and provide resources for ASEAN security
reserves which include keeping "a few thousand tons of rice in
their own countries as reserves in case of a need on the ASEAN
basis."
</P>
<P>
The Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) groups
Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia, the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand
and Vietnam. It will admit Laos and Myanmar on July 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
