<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Tamil Rebels Assassinate Muslim MP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 20 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's rebels of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) today shot dead Muslim
opposition member of Parliament M.A.H. Maharoof and five others in
Trincomalee Town in Eastern Province of the country, according to
informed sources here.
</P>
<P>
Maharoof, who belongs to the main opposition United National
Party (UNP), and his entourage were traveling in a jeep from his
residence to his office when they were ambushed by the LTTE
rebels.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels shot dead Maharoof and his supporters in the
jeep in which they were traveling, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first attack by the LTTE on an UNP MP since the
present government took office in 1994. Two weeks ago, the LTTE
Killed Tamil United Liberation front MP A. Thangathurai and four
others after a ceremony at a school also in Trincomalee Town.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been fighting a 14-year war for a
separate Tamil state in the north and east of the country.
</P>
