<HEADLINE> Over 700 Drug Traffickers Nabbed in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 20 (Xinhua) -- More than 700 drug traffickers
have been detained and drugs with a combined street value of 2.9
million US Dollars were seized in Zambia in the first six months
of this year, Sunday Times of Zambia reported today.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman of the Drug Enforcement Commission (DEC) of Zambia,
Mukutulu Sinyani was quoted as saying that out of the 718 drug
traffickers nabbed, 294 had been convicted and were currently
serving various jail terms while the remainder of the cases had
almost been concluded.
</P>
<P>
Sinyani said that out of the drug traffickers arrested, 691
were Zambians while the rest were from the Democratic Republic of
Congo, Malawi, Britain, Ghana, South Africa, Greece, Japan and
Nigeria.
</P>
<P>
The drugs seized included 8.5 tons of marijuana, 22 kilograms
of hashish, seven kilograms of cannabis seeds, one kilogram of
khat or miraa, 135 grams lidocaine which is a derivative of
cocaine, and 80 grams of LSD which is a deadly hallucinongen.
</P>
