recommended the publishing of the bill and the repeal of 11 laws
which have been widely described as "oppressive and colonial."
</P>
<P>
The move is seen as a surprise departure from the
uncompromising stand, previously adopted by KANU which has an
absolute majority in parliament, against legal and constitutional
reforms.
</P>
<P>
The laws charged as "oppressive" include the Public Order Act
on public rallies, the Preservation of Public Security Act, the
Penal Code and so on. 
