<HEADLINE> Uganda to Vaccinate Cattle </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, July 20 (Xinhua ) -- The Ugandan ministry of
agriculture has decided to launch an immunisation campaign
against two cattle diseases on August 6 this year.
</P>
<P>
The two diseases are rinderpest and bovine pleuropneumonia
(cbpp).
</P>
<P>
A press release issued here yesterday by the ministry was
quoted by Sunday Monitor today as saying that the campaign to
save Uganda's 5.3 million cattle will end in October this year.
</P>
<P>
The two diseases are highly infectious killer cattle diseases#,
but curable, the release said.
</P>
<P>
Rinderpest is an infectious virus disease which affects
cattle and wild game like buffalos, while cbpp affects the lungs
of the animal.
</P>
<P>
The release said the vaccination campaign will run
simultaneously throughout the country. 
</P>
