<DATE_TIME> 1997-07-20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pivotals Suffer Severe Setback on BSE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 20 (Xinhua)-- Pivotals suffered a severe
setback on the Bombay Stock Exchange (BSE) market as well as on
the National Stock market last week due to political uncertainty
in the country.
</P>
<P>
The sensitive index crashed 197 points during the week. The
trading sentiment was steady when it resumed on Monday but
suddenly turned weak on all round liquidation. Since then the
market has never recovered and selling pressure continued.
</P>
<P>
The BSE sensitive index slumped from the previous week level of
4321.98 to 4124.81 with the sizable loss of 197.17 points. The
national index also lost 83.31 points to 1791.93 from the previous
week level of 1875.24.
</P>
<P>
The trading sentiment was considerably affected following a
decision by the Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam (DMK), one of the
constituents of the ruling United Front, to withdraw its ministers
from the Inder Kumar Gujral government. The uncertain political
situation continued throughout the week. As a result, the
speculative activities reduced considerably and foreign
institutions have also slowed down their buying. The selling
pressure was also due to a likely hike in petroleum prices in the
coming days.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
