<HEADLINE> EIB Extends Loans to Czech Republic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The European Investment Bank (EIB)
has agreed to extend a loan for building the Czech section of the
sixth railway line connecting Northern and Southern Europe.
</P>
<P>
Czech Finance Minister Ivan Pilip and the EIB's Vice President
Wolfgang Roth signed here today the loan agreement worth 200
million Ecus (about 254 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
In addition, the EIB will offer three billion korunas (about
909 million dollars) in loans to the Czech Republic for highway
construction projects inside the country.
</P>
<P>
Some infrastructure projects in the Czech Republic are faced
with the threat of suspension as budget for the sector has been
cut down due to financial difficulties.
</P>
<P>
To secure these projects, the Czech Republic obtained two
billion dollars in low-interest loans in June from an
international group of 24 banks. 
</P>
