<HEADLINE> Latin American Cultural News Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, July 19 (Xinhua) -- The following are news briefs
about recent culture, arts and entertainment events in Latin
America in the past few days:
</P>
<P>
PANAMA CITY -- The first Continental Cinematographic Festival
is scheduled for October 5-10 in the Panamanian capital.
</P>
<P>
The festival is expected to screen latest Hollywood movies and
the Panamanian public will serve as the jury to award the prizes
of best picture and best director.
</P>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA -- An exhibition of paintings by Manuel
Quintana Castillo, a Venezuelan artist known across Latin America,
was held this week at the Santafe de Bogota Museum of Modern Art.
</P>
<P>
In dozens of paintings at the event, entitled "To Bathe in the
Same River," the artist shows his personal pictorial concept,
impressing Colombian art connoisseurs with his rich images.
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Several funerary urns from pre-Columbus times
containing human remains and rests of animals, such as deer, fish,
iguanas and turtle shells, have been found in Managua.
</P>
<P>
U.S. anthropologist Frederick William Lange, who coordinates
the U.S.-Nicaraguan joint discovery, said the human remains were
dated back to 1350, or two centuries before the Spanish conquest.
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- The International Film Festival of short feature
movies is scheduled for August in the Chilean capital with the
participation of Chilean and foreign film makers.
</P>
<P>
The festival aims at supporting the increasing production of
short feature movies worldwide, and to help young producers'
efforts to distribute and market their work.
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- The Selection and Awarding Committee of
Photography Contest in 1997 announced the three winners of the
event and awarded each of them more than 3,000 U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
The three prizes were won by "Paradeisos" of Laura Barron
Echauri, "El Beso Esencial II, III, and IV" of Edgar Ladron de
Guevara Cervantes, and "De la Calle al Estudio" of Pedro Slim.
</P>
