<HEADLINE> Chinese Manufacturer Eyes Overseas Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The Kelon Group, one of China's
largest household appliance manufacturers, intends to become the
world's leading refrigerator maker, the China Daily reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Guangdong-baded group plans to expand its international
business while increasing production to achieve that goal.
</P>
<P>
It has maintained the title of the country's largest
refrigerator maker for six years. Last year, it sold 1.8 million
refrigerators.
</P>
<P>
Group president Pan Ning said last week his group planned to
move its headquarters to Hong Kong from Shunde, Guangdong, to
capitalize on Hong Kong's advantages as a global information,
trade and financial center.
</P>
<P>
The group spent more than 100 million yuan ($12 million) on an
office building in Hong Kong. It spent more than 100 million yuan
establishing the Kelon (Japan) Ltd. in Kobe last year.
</P>
<P>
In the domestic market, it spent 510 million yuan ($61.44
million) establishing two refrigerator plants in Chengdu, Sichuan
Province and Yingkou, Liaoning Province, in December 1996 to
increase its annual output of freon-free refrigerators by one
million sets.  
