<HEADLINE> Colombia Exports 150,000 Barrels of Crude Oil a Day </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Colombia exported an
average of 150,000 barrels of crude oil a day in the first half of
this year, the country's state oil company said today.
</P>
<P>
The daily export, said the company, known as Ecopetrol, in a
report, was similar to the figure for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Colombia exported fuel oil, diesel, naphtha and
other oil products at a rate of 77,000 barrels a day; and imported
28,613 barrels of oil products a day, specially motor gasoline.
</P>
<P>
Ecopetrol earned 738 million U.S. dollars from the exports and
paid 144 million dollars for the imports in the year's first half,
resulting in a trade surplus of 593 million at the end of June.
</P>
