<HEADLINE> Hall Commemorating Chinese Communist Party Founder Built </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 20 (Xinhua) -- A hall commemorating Li
Dazhao, a founder of the Chinese Communist Party and a great
Marxist, has been set up in north China's Hebei Province.
</P>
<P>
The memorial hall with a floor space of 4,680 square meters was
built on a seven-hectare plot in Li's hometown of Leting Count.
</P>
<P>
The county has launched a collection drive to get memorabilia
from Li's life since work on the hall began 11 months ago. It has
collected 1,000 items including photos, letters, manuscripts,
newspapers, magazines and stationery related to Li's life.
