<HEADLINE> Korda Advances to Final in Washington Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Second-seeded Czech Petr Korda
reached the final of the ATP Washington Classic, defeating
American qualifier David Wheaton 6-2, 6-3 here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The 21th seed will take on the winner of a later semi-final
between defending champion and world number two Michael Chang of
the United States and New Zealand's Brett Steven for Sunday's
final.
</P>
<P>
It is the second final of the year for the Czech, who took the
trophy here in 1992. He lost the other last month in Halle to
Yevgeny Kafelnikov.
</P>
<P>
Wheaton, ranked 232nd, saw his only break point came in the
seventh game of the second set but Korda never gave away to take
the match in 80 minutes. 
