<HEADLINE> China Invests More in Fixed Assets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- China invested 356.3 billion yuan
in fixed assets during the first five months this year, up 14
percent over the same period in 1996, according to the latest
statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
During the January-May period, the country poured 206 billion
yuan into capital construction, up 20.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
The investment in technical updating and transformation reached
67.3 billion yuan, up 15.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
That in real estate was 65.1 billion yuan, down 2.9 percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
