<HEADLINE> State Investment in Agriculture Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from the
State Statistics Bureau show that China invested 9.94 billion yuan
in the primary industry, which includes farming, forestry, animal
husbandry, fishery and water conservancy, during the first five
months this year, up 98.3 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country's investment in secondary industry,
primarily the manufacturing industry, reached 150.9 billion yuan,
up 11.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The investment in tertiary industry, or the service sector,
came to 193.5 billion yuan, up 13.7 percent.  
</P>
