<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Five Thousand Evacuated Near Derailment in U.S. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Five thousand residents in and
around Flora, Mississippi, have been evacuated as a 25-car train
with hazardous chemical stored derailed, the United Press
International reported today.
</P>
<P>
Authorities plan a controlled explosion of more than 300,000
pounds of the potentially hazardous chemical stored in two
refrigerated cars.
</P>
<P>
The Illinois Central Railroad train derailed Friday afternoon.
Although much of the derailment has been cleaned up, those two
cars pose a significant threat as chloroprene is a very sensitive
chemical with a flashpoint of minus four Celsius and given the
wave of 90 degree temperatures, could explode all by itself.
</P>
<P>
With explosive charges, authorities plan to rupture the cars,
then ignite it. 
</P>
</TEXT>
