<HEADLINE> Seles Quits from New Jersey Classic </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Monica Seles abandoned the
semifinals of the Women's Tennis Classic in New Jersey on Saturday
due to back injuries.
</P>
<P>
Thus, Chandra Rubin who ranked 29th, advanced to the finals and
would play 16-year-old Anna Kournikova of Russia for the title.
</P>
<P>
Suffering from back spasms through most of the match, Seles
bade farewell from the tournament when she was leading 6-3, 2-3.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova was the budding star from Russia who reached the
semifinals at Wimbledon before Losing to Martina Hingis.
</P>
<P>
Kournikova beat Maggie Maleeva of Bulgaria 6-4, 6-1 on Saturday
to secure her outing to the finals.
</P>
<P>
Seles has been plagued with injuries since returning to the
tour two years ago after a 28-month layoff.
</P>
<P>
Last year at the Australian Open, Seles injured her left
shoulder. 
</P>
</TEXT>
