<HEADLINE> Slovak Kucera Dumps Brugera out of Stuttgart </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Unseeded Karol Kucera of Slovakia
prevented a Spanish sweep in the last four by defeating fourth
seed Sergi Brugera 6-3, 2-6, 7-5 to reach the semifinals of the
Stuttgart clay-court tournament on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Play in their quarter-final was delayed for several hours
because of heavy rain, which also forced organisers to postpone
the semifinals from Saturday to Sunday morning, with the final to
be played in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Kucera will take on Spaniard Albert Portas in the semifinals,
who beat 10th-seeded compatriot Felix Mantilla 6-2, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Albert Costa meets third-seeded fellow Spaniard Alex Corretja
in the other semifinal. 
