<HEADLINE> China's Computer Industry in Mixed Change in January-May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- The latest statistics from State
Statistical Bureau show that China's fledgling computer industry
changed mixedly during the first five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
During that period, the output of electronic computers reached
520 units, up 296.9 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the country manufactured 282,500 micro-electronic
computers, down 4.5 percent.  
</P>
