<HEADLINE> China's Freight Traffic Volume Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 20 (Xinhua) -- China's freight traffic volume stood
at 1.1 billion tons during the first five months this year, down
1.4 percent over the same period in 1996, according to the latest
statistics from the State Statistical Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The freight traffic volume of railways was 668 million tons, a
year-on-year decrease of 1.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of motor vehicles was 177 million tons, down 2.7 percent,
and that of civil aviation, 488,000 tons, up eight percent.
</P>
</TEXT>
