<HEADLINE> France Comes out on Top in Fencing Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 19 (Xinhua) -- France obtained the team
sabre gold to finish atop the medals tally at the World Fencing
Championships in the South African city Cape Town on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The team win took its title tally to three -- after victories
in the men's individual epee and men's team foil -- to add to four
bronze medals.
</P>
<P>
Cuba finished second with two golds and two silvers, with Italy
third with two golds, one silver and three bronze.
</P>
<P>
Facing a Russian sabre team including world and Olympic
champion Sergei Pozdniakov, France finally edged to a narrow 45-42
victory.
</P>
<P>
Pozdniakov closed an eight-point gap to two in the final bout
before world number two Damien Touya completed victory for France.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Hungary won its first gold medal of the championships
when it defeated Germany 45-40 in the final of the women's team
epee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
