<HEADLINE> Kenyan Komen Sets World Record for Two Miles </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 19 (Xinhua) -- Daniel Komen of Kenya set a world
best time for the two miles when he clocked seven minutes 58.61
seconds at the Hechtel international meeting on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Komen beat the previous time of 8:01.08 set by Ethiopia's Haile
Gebrselassie at Hengelo in the Netherlands on May 31.
</P>
<P>
It was the third time in five years that the two-mile mark was
improved in this small meet in eastern Belgium, after Morocco's
Khalid Skah and Kenyan Moses Kiptanui set new marks in 1993 and
1994.
</P>
<P>
The 21-year-old Kenyan is also the world record holder in the
3,000 meters. 
</P>
</TEXT>
