<HEADLINE> US Soldier Wounded in Bomb Attack in Bosnia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SARAJEVO,July 19 (Xinhua)-- A U.S. soldier serving with
NATO-led Stabilization Force(SFOR) was slightly injured when a
bomb exploded Friday night in the Serb-controlled town of Doboj,
according to local press reports.
</P>
<P>
The soldier was cut by flying glass after an explosive device
was thrown at a car parked outside the offices used by SFOR
military observers in the central Bosnian town.
</P>
<P>
This is the second U.S. soldier wounded by hostile action in
the Serb entity since a NATO special force killed one Serb war
crime indictee and captured another in its first of such operation
on July 10.
</P>
<P>
Three days ago, another U.S. soldier was wounded by an
unidentified man with a sickle in Kladanj, northeastern Bosnia.
</P>
<P>
Since NATO's "Tango" operation, there has been almost daily
what was described "lower-level harassment" against SFOR and
international organizations in the Serb republic, which including
bombings and calls of threat.
</P>
<P>
But except the two U.S. soldier, no one was injured in those
incidents. 
</P>
</TEXT>
